               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280911-377-cd1956" type="crimeDate">17th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-377-off1955 t18280911-377-cd1956"></join>, 19 shillings, and 15d. in copper monies
            </rs>, the monies of 
               <persName id="t18280911-377-victim2038" type="victimName">
                  Richard 
                  Tomlinson
               <interp inst="t18280911-377-victim2038" type="surname" value="Tomlinson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-377-victim2038" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-377-victim2038" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-377-off1955 t18280911-377-victim2038"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>RICHARD TOMLINSON. I am a <rs id="t18280911-377-viclabel1957" type="occupation">simpler for the chemists</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-377-victim2038 t18280911-377-viclabel1957"></join>. On the 17th of August, between two and three o'clock in the afternoon, I went to a public-house, and had a pot of beer: I fell asleep, and had 19s. in silver, and about 2s. 6d. in copper, in my pocket - I had seen the prisoner before I went to sleep, and when I awoke my silver was gone from my left hand trousers pocket, and my copper from the right; the prisoner had left the place; he came to the same house in about a week, and instead of asking my pardon, he was rather saucy, and I had him taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-377-person2039">
                  JOHN 
                  DICKS
               <interp inst="t18280911-377-person2039" type="surname" value="DICKS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-377-person2039" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-377-person2039" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a coal-porter. On the 17th of August I was in the <placeName id="t18280911-377-crimeloc1958">Blue Boar public-house, Cock-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-377-crimeloc1958" type="placeName" value="Blue Boar public-house, Cock-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-377-crimeloc1958" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-377-off1955 t18280911-377-crimeloc1958"></join>; the prisoner went and sat by the side of Tomlinson, and soon after I saw his hand in his pocket; I said I would not see such a thing done where I was - he jumped up, and challenged me to fight; after some time he came and sat down, and took up a bag which fell out of the prosecutor's hat, which was on the table; I got up, and went to another part of the room; when the prosecutor awoke he was gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-377-person2040">
                  JOHN 
                  SHEPHERD
               <interp inst="t18280911-377-person2040" type="surname" value="SHEPHERD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-377-person2040" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-377-person2040" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner take a simple bag out of the prosecutor's hat; Dicks said, "What business have you with it?" he said, "I will let you see."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-377-person2041">
                  CHARLES 
                  STEED
               <interp inst="t18280911-377-person2041" type="surname" value="STEED"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-377-person2041" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-377-person2041" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. On the 27th of<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182809110176"></xptr>August, I was passing the Blue Boar, and the prosecutor said, "Here is a man who has robbed me ten days ago:" the prisoner came out, and went down a court; the prosecutor said he was the man - I took him, and found nothing on him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I never moved from the post. Witness. Yes; he tried to escape.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went there to have a pot of beer; I went out, and came in again. <rs id="t18280911-377-verdict1959" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-377-verdict1959" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
